<p>I&rsquo;ve been making a web application where I haven&rsquo;t ironed out my database
schema yet so I wanted a migration tool to tweak it as I change my mind.</p>
<p>Someone on Mastodon recommended <a href="https://github.com/amacneil/dbmate">dbmate</a>
recently and it&rsquo;s been working well. Here&rsquo;s how I use it:</p>
<ol>
<li>Run <code>dbmate new my_migration</code></li>
<li>Edit the migration file to</li>
<li>Run <code>dbmate up</code> to apply it</li>
</ol>
<p>Then I can run <code>dbmate up</code> in production too. I&rsquo;ve only been doing &ldquo;up&rdquo; migrations, no &ldquo;down&rdquo; migrations.</p>
